{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841816028,"sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","part":{"id":"prt_d786b9c1600103tNRJtvX4Ph0d","messageID":"msg_d786b930b00120r4eikhbU3AIX","sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-002  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Small  \n9: \n10: Define the Go type definitions for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets safely within Kubernetes.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: The CodeInterpreter type extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n19: \n20: ```\n21: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n22: │                    Kubernetes API Server                         │\n23: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n24: │  │  runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1                  │   │\n25: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐   │   │\n26: │  │  │ AgentRuntime│  │         CodeInterpreter         │   │   │\n27: │  │  │             │  │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │   │   │\n28: │  │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  │  │ CodeInterpreterSpec       │  │   │   │\n29: │  │  │ │ Image   │ │  │  │ - Image (required)        │  │   │   │\n30: │  │  │ │ Resources│ │  │  │ - Language (enum)         │  │   │   │\n31: │  │  │ │ Ports   │ │  │  │ - Resources (optional)    │  │   │   │\n32: │  │  │ │ ...     │ │  │  │ - TimeoutSeconds          │  │   │   │\n33: │  │  │ └─────────┘ │  │  │ - MaxMemoryMB             │  │   │   │\n34: │  │  │             │  │  │ - Env                     │  │   │   │\n35: │  │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  │  └───────────────────────────┘  │   │   │\n36: │  │  │ │ Status  │ │  │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │   │   │\n37: │  │  │ │ Phase   │ │  │  │ CodeInterpreterStatus     │  │   │   │\n38: │  │  │ │ ...     │ │  │  │ - Phase (enum)            │  │   │   │\n39: │  │  │ └─────────┘ │  │  │ - Conditions              │  │   │   │\n40: │  │  └─────────────┘  │  │ - SandboxID               │  │   │   │\n41: │  │                   │  │ - ExecutionCount          │  │   │   │\n42: │  │                   │  └───────────────────────────┘  │   │   │\n43: │  │                   └─────────────────────────────────┘   │   │\n44: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                               │\n47:                               ▼\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                    Generated client-go                          │\n50: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │\n51: │  │   Clientset     │  │    Informers    │  │    Listers      │ │\n52: │  │                 │  │                 │  │                 │ │\n53: │  │ · Interface     │  │ · SharedInformer│  │ · Lister        │ │\n54: │  │ · Create/Get/...│  │   Factory       │  │ · NamespaceList │ │\n55: │  └─────────────────┘  │ · Per-type      │  └─────────────────┘ │\n56: │                       │   informers     │                      │\n57: │                       └─────────────────┘                      │\n58: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### Component Interactions\n62: \n63: 1. **Type Definitions** (`codeinterpreter_types.go`): Go structs with kubebuilder markers\n64: 2. **Scheme Registration** (`register.go`): Adds types to the runtime scheme\n65: 3. **Code Generation**: `controller-gen` generates DeepCopy methods; `code-generator` creates client-go\n66: 4. **Client Consumers**: Workload Manager, CLI tools, external controllers\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## Data Structures\n71: \n72: ### Core Types\n73: \n74: #### CodeInterpreterPhase\n75: \n76: Enumeration representing the lifecycle phases of a CodeInterpreter.\n77: \n78: ```go\n79: // CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n80: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n81: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n82: type CodeInterpreterPhase string\n83: \n84: const (\n85:     // CodeInterpreterPhasePending indicates the interpreter is being provisioned.\n86:     CodeInterpreterPhasePending CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n87: \n88:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning indicates the interpreter is active and ready.\n89:     CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n90: \n91:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded indicates the interpreter completed successfully.\n92:     CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n93: \n94:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed indicates the interpreter failed.\n95:     CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n96: )\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### ProgrammingLanguage\n100: \n101: Enumeration of supported programming languages with validation.\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: // ProgrammingLanguage represents a supported programming language.\n105: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go;rust;java;cpp\n106: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n107: type ProgrammingLanguage string\n108: \n109: const (\n110:     LanguagePython     ProgrammingLanguage = \"python\"\n111:     LanguageJavaScript ProgrammingLanguage = \"javascript\"\n112:     LanguageTypeScript ProgrammingLanguage = \"typescript\"\n113:     LanguageGo         ProgrammingLanguage = \"go\"\n114:     LanguageRust       ProgrammingLanguage = \"rust\"\n115:     LanguageJava       ProgrammingLanguage = \"java\"\n116:     LanguageCpp        ProgrammingLanguage = \"cpp\"\n117: )\n118: ```\n119: \n120: #### CodeInterpreterSpec\n121: \n122: Configuration for code execution environment.\n123: \n124: ```go\n125: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n126: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n127:     // Image is the container image to use for the interpreter sandbox.\n128:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n129:     // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n130:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n131: \n132:     // Language specifies the programming language for the interpreter.\n133:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n134:     Language ProgrammingLanguage `json:\"language\"`\n135: \n136:     // RuntimeClassName specifies the runtime class for sandbox configuration.\n137:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n138:     RuntimeClassName string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n139: \n140:     // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n141:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n142:     Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n143: \n144:     // Storage defines persistent storage configuration for the interpreter.\n145:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n146:     Storage *CodeInterpreterStorageSpec `json:\"storage,omitempty\"`\n147: \n148:     // SecurityContext defines pod-level security settings.\n149:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n150:     SecurityContext *corev1.SecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n151: \n152:     // NetworkPolicy defines network isolation configuration.\n153:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n154:     NetworkPolicy *CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec `json:\"networkPolicy,omitempty\"`\n155: \n156:     // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds).\n157:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n158:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n159:     // +kubebuilder:default=300\n160:     TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n161: \n162:     // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) for code execution.\n163:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n164:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n165:     // +kubebuilder:default=512\n166:     MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n167: \n168:     // AllowedImports defines the whitelist of allowed package imports.\n169:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n170:     // +listType=set\n171:     AllowedImports []string `json:\"allowedImports,omitempty\"`\n172: \n173:     // Env defines environment variables for the sandbox container.\n174:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n175:     // +listType=map\n176:     // +listMapKey=name\n177:     Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: #### CodeInterpreterStorageSpec\n182: \n183: Persistent storage configuration.\n184: \n185: ```go\n186: // CodeInterpreterStorageSpec defines storage configuration for CodeInterpreter.\n187: type CodeInterpreterStorageSpec struct {\n188:     // Size is the storage size (e.g., \"1Gi\", \"10Gi\").\n189:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n190:     Size resource.Quantity `json:\"size\"`\n191: \n192:     // StorageClassName specifies the storage class for the volume.\n193:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n194:     StorageClassName string `json:\"storageClassName,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196:     // AccessMode specifies the access mode for the volume.\n197:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n198:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=ReadWriteOnce;ReadOnlyMany;ReadWriteMany\n199:     // +kubebuilder:default=ReadWriteOnce\n200:     AccessMode string `json:\"accessMode,omitempty\"`\n201: }\n202: ```\n203: \n204: #### CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec\n205: \n206: Network isolation configuration.\n207: \n208: ```go\n209: // CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec defines network policy for CodeInterpreter.\n210: type CodeInterpreterNetworkPolicySpec struct {\n211:     // IngressRules defines allowed ingress traffic.\n212:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n213:     // +listType=atomic\n214:     IngressRules []NetworkPolicyRule `json:\"ingressRules,omitempty\"`\n215: \n216:     // EgressRules defines allowed egress traffic.\n217:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n218:     // +listType=atomic\n219:     EgressRules []NetworkPolicyRule `json:\"egressRules,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // NetworkPolicyRule defines a network policy rule.\n223: type NetworkPolicyRule struct {\n224:     // From specifies the source of traffic.\n225:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n226:     From string `json:\"from,omitempty\"`\n227: \n228:     // To specifies the destination of traffic.\n229:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n230:     To string `json:\"to,omitempty\"`\n231: \n232:     // Ports specifies the allowed ports.\n233:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n234:     // +listType=atomic\n235:     Ports []int32 `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n236: }\n237: ```\n238: \n239: #### CodeInterpreterStatus\n240: \n241: Observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n242: \n243: ```go\n244: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n245: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n246:     // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n247:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n248:     Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n249: \n250:     // Conditions represents the latest available observations.\n251:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n252:     // +listType=map\n253:     // +listMapKey=type\n254:     // +patchMergeKey=type\n255:     // +patchStrategy=merge\n256:     Conditions []CodeInterpreterCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n257: \n258:     // InterpreterURL is the endpoint URL for the interpreter service.\n259:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n260:     InterpreterURL string `json:\"interpreterURL,omitempty\"`\n261: \n262:     // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n263:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n264:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n265: \n266:     // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n267:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n268:     LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n269: \n270:     // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n271:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n272:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n273:     ExecutionCount int64 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n274: \n275:     // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n276:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n277:     Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n278: \n279:     // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n280:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n281:     Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n282: \n283:     // ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed.\n284:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n285:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n286:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n287: }\n288: ```\n289: \n290: #### CodeInterpreterCondition\n291: \n292: Condition type for status reporting.\n293: \n294: ```go\n295: // CodeInterpreterConditionType represents a condition type.\n296: type CodeInterpreterConditionType string\n297: \n298: const (\n299:     // CodeInterpreterConditionReady indicates the interpreter is ready.\n300:     CodeInterpreterConditionReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Ready\"\n301: \n302:     // CodeInterpreterConditionStorageReady indicates storage is provisioned.\n303:     CodeInterpreterConditionStorageReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"StorageReady\"\n304: \n305:     // CodeInterpreterConditionRuntimeReady indicates the runtime is ready.\n306:     CodeInterpreterConditionRuntimeReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"RuntimeReady\"\n307: \n308:     // CodeInterpreterConditionExecutionAvailable indicates execution is available.\n309:     CodeInterpreterConditionExecutionAvailable CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"ExecutionAvailable\"\n310: )\n311: \n312: // CodeInterpreterCondition represents a condition of a CodeInterpreter.\n313: type CodeInterpreterCondition struct {\n314:     // Type is the type of the condition.\n315:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n316:     Type CodeInterpreterConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n317: \n318:     // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n319:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n320:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n321:     Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n322: \n323:     // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n324:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n325:     LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n326: \n327:     // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n328:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n329:     Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n330: \n331:     // Message is a human-readable message.\n332:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n333:     Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n334: }\n335: ```\n336: \n337: #### Root Types\n338: \n339: ```go\n340: // +genclient\n341: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n342: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n343: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n344: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n345: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n346: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Language\",type=string,JSONPath=`.spec.language`,description=\"Programming language\"\n347: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n348: \n349: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n350: // A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\n351: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n352:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n353:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n354: \n355:     // Spec defines the desired state of the CodeInterpreter.\n356:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n357:     Spec CodeInterpreterSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n358: \n359:     // Status defines the observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n360:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n361:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n362: }\n363: \n364: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n365: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n366: \n367: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n368: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n369:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n370:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n371: \n372:     // Items is the list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n373:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n374:     Items []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ---\n379: \n380: ## API Contracts\n381: \n382: ### REST Resource Contract\n383: \n384: | Property | Value |\n385: |----------|-------|\n386: | API Group | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n387: | Version | `v1alpha1` |\n388: | Kind | `CodeInterpreter` |\n389: | Plural | `codeinterpreters` |\n390: | Singular | `codeinterpreter` |\n391: | Short Names | `ci`, `cis` |\n392: | Scope | Namespaced |\n393: | Categories | `agentcube`, `all` |\n394: \n395: ### HTTP Endpoints (Kubernetes API Server)\n396: \n397: | Method | Path | Description |\n398: |--------|------|-------------|\n399: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n400: | POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n401: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n402: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n403: | PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Patch CodeInterpreter |\n404: | DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n405: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get Status subresource |\n406: | PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update Status subresource |\n407: | GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/codeinterpreters` | List all (cluster-scoped) |\n408: \n409: ### Generated Client Interface\n410: \n411: ```go\n412: // CodeInterpretersGetter provides access to CodeInterpreter resources.\n413: type CodeInterpretersGetter interface {\n414:     CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n415: }\n416: \n417: // CodeInterpreterInterface provides CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter.\n418: type CodeInterpreterInterface interface {\n419:     Create(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n420:     Update(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n421:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n422:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n423:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n424:     Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n425:     List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n426:     Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n427:     Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n428:     CodeInterpreterExpansion\n429: }\n430: ```\n431: \n432: ### Validation Rules\n433: \n434: | Field | Rule | Error Message |\n435: |-------|------|---------------|\n436: | `spec.image` | Required, MinLength=1 | `\"Image is required\"` |\n437: | `spec.language` | Required, Enum validation | `\"Invalid language\"` |\n438: | `spec.timeoutSeconds` | Minimum=1, Default=300 | `\"Timeout must be >= 1\"` |\n439: | `spec.maxMemoryMB` | Minimum=64, Default=512 | `\"Memory must be >= 64MB\"` |\n440: | `spec.storage.size` | Required if storage specified | `\"Storage size is required\"` |\n441: | `spec.storage.accessMode` | Enum: ReadWriteOnce/ReadOnlyMany/ReadWriteMany | `\"Invalid access mode\"` |\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ## Error Handling\n446: \n447: ### Type-Level Errors\n448: \n449: 1. **Validation Errors**: Kubernetes API server returns validation errors for invalid spec values\n450: 2. **Scheme Registration Errors**: Runtime errors if types not properly registered\n451: 3. **DeepCopy Errors**: Panic if DeepCopy methods not generated\n452: \n453: ### Error Categories\n454: \n455: | Category | Source | Handling Strategy |\n456: |----------|--------|-------------------|\n457: | Schema Validation | Kubebuilder markers | API server rejects with 422 |\n458: | Type Conversion | runtime.Object interface | Compile-time checking |\n459: | Serialization | JSON marshaling | Return error to caller |\n460: | Code Generation | controller-gen | CI/CD failure, fix and regenerate |\n461: \n462: ### Error Propagation\n463: \n464: ```go\n465: // Example error handling pattern for client usage\n466: func (c *CodeInterpreterClient) SafeCreate(ctx context.Context, ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n467:     // Validate before sending\n468:     if err := validateCodeInterpreter(ci); err != nil {\n469:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"validation failed: %w\", err)\n470:     }\n471: \n472:     result, err := c.client.CodeInterpreters(ci.Namespace).Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n473:     if err != nil {\n474:         // Check for specific Kubernetes errors\n475:         if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n476:             return nil, ErrCodeInterpreterExists\n477:         }\n478:         if apierrors.IsInvalid(err) {\n479:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid spec: %w\", err)\n480:         }\n481:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create failed: %w\", err)\n482:     }\n483: \n484:     return result, nil\n485: }\n486: ```\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Testing Strategy\n491: \n492: ### Unit Tests\n493: \n494: #### Type Definition Tests\n495: \n496: Located in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go`:\n497: \n498: ```go\n499: func TestCodeInterpreterImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n500:     ci := &CodeInterpreter{}\n501:     var _ runtime.Object = ci // Compile-time assertion\n502: }\n503: \n504: func TestCodeInterpreterListImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n505:     list := &CodeInterpreterList{}\n506:     var _ runtime.Object = list // Compile-time assertion\n507: }\n508: \n509: func TestCodeInterpreterDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n510:     original := &CodeInterpreter{\n511:         Spec: CodeInterpreterSpec{\n512:             Image:    \"python:3.11\",\n513:             Language: LanguagePython,\n514:             TimeoutSeconds: func() *int32 { i := int32(300); return &i }(),\n515:         },\n516:     }\n517: \n518:     copied := original.DeepCopy()\n519: \n520:     // Verify copy is independent\n521:     *copied.Spec.TimeoutSeconds = 600\n522:     assert.Equal(t, int32(300), *original.Spec.TimeoutSeconds)\n523: }\n524: \n525: func TestProgrammingLanguageValidation(t *testing.T) {\n526:     validLanguages := []ProgrammingLanguage{\n527:         LanguagePython, LanguageJavaScript, LanguageTypeScript,\n528:         LanguageGo, LanguageRust, LanguageJava, LanguageCpp,\n529:     }\n530: \n531:     for _, lang := range validLanguages {\n532:         assert.NotEmpty(t, lang)\n533:     }\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ### Integration Tests\n538: \n539: #### Scheme Registration Test\n540: \n541: ```go\n542: func TestCodeInterpreterSchemeRegistration(t *testing.T) {\n543:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n544:     err := v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n545:     require.NoError(t, err)\n546: \n547:     // Verify CodeInterpreter is registered\n548:     gv := v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion\n549:     gvk := gv.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n550:     obj, err := scheme.New(gvk)\n551:     require.NoError(t, err)\n552:     assert.IsType(t, &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}, obj)\n553: }\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ### Code Generation Verification\n557: \n558: ```bash\n559: #!/bin/bash\n560: # verify-codegen.sh\n561: \n562: # Generate code\n563: make generate\n564: \n565: # Verify compilation\n566: go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n567: \n568: # Verify tests pass\n569: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n570: \n571: # Check no uncommitted changes\n572: if [[ -n $(git status --porcelain pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go) ]]; then\n573:     echo \"ERROR: DeepCopy methods not up to date\"\n574:     exit 1\n575: fi\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ### Test Coverage Requirements\n579: \n580: | Component | Coverage Target |\n581: |-----------|-----------------|\n582: | Type definitions | 80%+ (struct validation) |\n583: | DeepCopy methods | Verified via generated code |\n584: | Scheme registration | 100% |\n585: | Client interfaces | Mock-based unit tests |\n586: \n587: ### Continuous Integration\n588: \n589: ```yaml\n590: # .github/workflows/test.yaml\n591: name: Test\n592: \n593: on: [push, pull_request]\n594: \n595: jobs:\n596:   test:\n597:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n598:     steps:\n599:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n600: \n601:       - name: Set up Go\n602:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n603:         with:\n604:           go-version: '1.24'\n605: \n606:       - name: Verify code generation\n607:         run: make verify-generate\n608: \n609:       - name: Build\n610:         run: go build ./pkg/apis/...\n611: \n612:       - name: Test\n613:         run: go test -v -race ./pkg/apis/...\n614: \n615:       - name: Lint\n616:         uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v6\n617:         with:\n618:           version: latest\n619: ```\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## File Layout\n624: \n625: ```\n626: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n627: ├── codeinterpreter_types.go      # CodeInterpreter type definitions (NEW)\n628: ├── agentruntime_types.go         # AgentRuntime type definitions (existing)\n629: ├── register.go                   # Scheme registration (MODIFIED)\n630: ├── doc.go                        # Package documentation\n631: ├── zz_generated.deepcopy.go      # Generated DeepCopy methods (GENERATED)\n632: └── codeinterpreter_types_test.go # Unit tests (NEW)\n633: ```\n634: \n635: ---\n636: \n637: ## Dependencies\n638: \n639: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n640: |------------|---------|---------|\n641: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, runtime.Object |\n642: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | ResourceRequirements, EnvVar, SecurityContext |\n643: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource` | `v0.34.1` | Quantity for storage sizes |\n644: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools` | `v0.17.2` | controller-gen for code generation |\n645: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go generation |\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ## Design Decisions\n650: \n651: ### 1. Separate CRD vs Extending AgentRuntime\n652: \n653: **Decision**: Create a separate `CodeInterpreter` CRD rather than extending `AgentRuntime`.\n654: \n655: **Rationale**:\n656: - CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics focused on code execution\n657: - Independent RBAC and scheduling policies\n658: - Client-go library explicitly defines separate interfaces (`CodeInterpretersGetter` vs `AgentRuntimesGetter`)\n659: - Supports language-specific optimizations and security policies\n660: \n661: ### 2. Controlled API Surface\n662: \n663: **Decision**: Define focused fields (`Image`, `Language`, `Resources`, `TimeoutSeconds`, etc.) rather than embedding full `PodSpec`.\n664: \n665: **Rationale**:\n666: - Guides users toward code execution best practices\n667: - Simplifies API surface\n668: - Enables language-specific validation and defaults\n669: - Maintains consistency with `AgentRuntime` pattern\n670: \n671: ### 3. Namespaced Scope\n672: \n673: **Decision**: CRD scope is `Namespaced`.\n674: \n675: **Rationale**:\n676: - Aligns with multi-tenant Kubernetes patterns\n677: - Enables namespace-level quotas and isolation\n678: - Consistent with `AgentRuntime` scope\n679: \n680: ### 4. Status Subresource\n681: \n682: **Decision**: Enable status subresource with `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`.\n683: \n684: **Rationale**:\n685: - Separation of concerns between spec and status\n686: - Enables RBAC to allow status updates without full object access\n687: - Standard Kubernetes pattern for controllers\n688: \n689: ---\n690: \n691: ## References\n692: \n693: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n694: - [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n695: - [Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n696: - [client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n697: \n698: ---\n699: \n700: ## Change Log\n701: \n702: | Version | Date | Changes |\n703: |---------|------|---------|\n704: | 1.0 | 2026-04-11 | Initial design for AR-002 CodeInterpreter CRD |\n\n(End of file - total 704 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-002  \n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small  \n\nDefine the Go type definitions for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets safely within Kubernetes.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\nThe CodeInterpreter type extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775841816007,"end":1775841816025}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841816035,"sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","part":{"id":"prt_d786ba003001pU5dtk40Y1hNWr","messageID":"msg_d786b930b00120r4eikhbU3AIX","sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n21: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n22: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n23: )\n24: \n25: var (\n26: \t// SchemeGroupVersion is the group version used to register these objects.\n27: \tSchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{\n28: \t\tGroup:   \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n29: \t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n30: \t}\n31: \n32: \t// SchemeBuilder is used to add types to the GroupVersion.\n33: \tSchemeBuilder = runtime.NewSchemeBuilder(addKnownTypes)\n34: \n35: \t// AddToScheme adds the types in this group-version to the given scheme.\n36: \tAddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n37: )\n38: \n39: // Resource takes an unqualified resource and returns a Group qualified GroupResource.\n40: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n41: \treturn SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n42: }\n43: \n44: // addKnownTypes adds the set of types defined in this package to the supplied scheme.\n45: func addKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n46: \tscheme.AddKnownTypes(\n47: \t\tSchemeGroupVersion,\n48: \t\t&AgentRuntime{},\n49: \t\t&AgentRuntimeList{},\n50: \t\t&CodeInterpreter{},\n51: \t\t&CodeInterpreterList{},\n52: \t)\n53: \tmetav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n54: \treturn nil\n55: }\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go","time":{"start":1775841816010,"end":1775841816034}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841816037,"sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","part":{"id":"prt_d786ba46b001d2Ck1Vv2GFZ78C","messageID":"msg_d786b930b00120r4eikhbU3AIX","sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // AgentRuntimePhase represents the current phase of an AgentRuntime.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// AgentRuntimePhasePending indicates the sandbox is being created.\n31: \tAgentRuntimePhasePending AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n32: \n33: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n34: \tAgentRuntimePhaseRunning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n35: \n36: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n37: \tAgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded AgentRuntimePhase = \"Succeeded\"\n38: \n39: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n40: \tAgentRuntimePhaseFailed AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n41: \n42: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n43: \tAgentRuntimePhaseUnknown AgentRuntimePhase = \"Unknown\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: // AgentRuntimeConditionType represents a condition type for AgentRuntime.\n47: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n48: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n49: type AgentRuntimeConditionType string\n50: \n51: const (\n52: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionReady indicates the AgentRuntime is ready to accept requests.\n53: \tAgentRuntimeConditionReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Ready\"\n54: \n55: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n56: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n57: \n58: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n59: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n60: \n61: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionFailed indicates the AgentRuntime has failed.\n62: \tAgentRuntimeConditionFailed AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Failed\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n66: // This specification describes the configuration for a sandbox instance\n67: // that will run an AI agent.\n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69: \t// Image is the container image to use for the sandbox.\n70: \t// This field is required and must be a valid container image reference.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n72: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n73: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n74: \n75: \t// Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n76: \t// If not specified, default resource limits will be applied.\n77: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n78: \tResources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n81: \t// These variables will be available to the running agent.\n82: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n83: \t// +listType=map\n84: \t// +listMapKey=name\n85: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n86: \n87: \t// Command overrides the default container entrypoint.\n88: \t// If not specified, the image's default entrypoint will be used.\n89: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n90: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n91: \n92: \t// Args provides arguments to the command or the default entrypoint.\n93: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n94: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n95: \n96: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory for the container.\n97: \t// If not specified, the container's default working directory will be used.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n100: \n101: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n102: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n103: \t// +listType=map\n104: \t// +listMapKey=containerPort\n105: \tPorts []corev1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n106: \n107: \t// VolumeMounts defines volumes to mount into the sandbox container.\n108: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n109: \t// +listType=map\n110: \t// +listMapKey=name\n111: \tVolumeMounts []corev1.VolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n112: \n113: \t// Volumes defines the volumes that can be mounted by the sandbox.\n114: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n115: \t// +listType=map\n116: \t// +listMapKey=name\n117: \tVolumes []corev1.Volume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n118: \n119: \t// ServiceAccountName specifies the service account to use for the sandbox pod.\n120: \t// If not specified, the default service account will be used.\n121: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n122: \tServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n123: \n124: \t// NodeSelector specifies node labels for pod scheduling.\n125: \t// The pod will only be scheduled on nodes matching these labels.\n126: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n127: \t// +mapType=atomic\n128: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// Tolerations allow the pod to be scheduled on nodes with matching taints.\n131: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n132: \t// +listType=atomic\n133: \tTolerations []corev1.Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n134: \n135: \t// Affinity defines the scheduling constraints for the pod.\n136: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n137: \tAffinity *corev1.Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n138: \n139: \t// TTLSecondsAfterFinished specifies the time to live (in seconds) after\n140: \t// the sandbox has finished (succeeded or failed). The sandbox will be\n141: \t// automatically deleted after this time.\n142: \t// If not specified, the sandbox will not be automatically deleted.\n143: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n144: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n145: \tTTLSecondsAfterFinished *int32 `json:\"ttlSecondsAfterFinished,omitempty\"`\n146: \n147: \t// IdleTimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum time (in seconds) the sandbox\n148: \t// can be idle before being terminated. If not specified, no idle timeout\n149: \t// is enforced.\n150: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n151: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n152: \tIdleTimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"idleTimeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// MaxLifetimeSeconds specifies the maximum lifetime (in seconds) of the sandbox.\n155: \t// The sandbox will be terminated after this duration regardless of activity.\n156: \t// If not specified, no maximum lifetime is enforced.\n157: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n158: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n159: \tMaxLifetimeSeconds *int32 `json:\"maxLifetimeSeconds,omitempty\"`\n160: }\n161: \n162: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n163: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n164: // state of the sandbox instance.\n165: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n166: \t// Phase represents the current phase of the AgentRuntime.\n167: \t// Possible values: Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tPhase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's state.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \t// +listType=map\n174: \t// +listMapKey=type\n175: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n176: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n177: \tConditions []AgentRuntimeCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n178: \n179: \t// SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n180: \t// This is set once the sandbox pod has been successfully created.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// PodName is the name of the pod running the sandbox.\n185: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n186: \tPodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// PodIP is the IP address assigned to the sandbox pod.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tPodIP string `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// StartTime is the time when the sandbox was started.\n193: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n194: \tStartTime *metav1.Time `json:\"startTime,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// CompletionTime is the time when the sandbox completed (succeeded or failed).\n197: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n198: \tCompletionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"completionTime,omitempty\"`\n199: \n200: \t// LastActivityTime is the time of the last activity in the sandbox.\n201: \t// Used for idle timeout tracking.\n202: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n203: \tLastActivityTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastActivityTime,omitempty\"`\n204: \n205: \t// Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n206: \t// This may contain error messages or other status information.\n207: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n208: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n209: \n210: \t// Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n211: \t// This is typically a CamelCase string indicating why the phase is set.\n212: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n213: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n214: \n215: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n216: \t// This is used to determine if the spec has been processed.\n217: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n218: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n219: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // AgentRuntimeCondition represents a condition of an AgentRuntime.\n223: type AgentRuntimeCondition struct {\n224: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n225: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n226: \tType AgentRuntimeConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n227: \n228: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n229: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n230: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n231: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n232: \n233: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n234: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n235: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n236: \n237: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n238: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n239: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n242: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n243: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n244: }\n245: \n246: // +genclient\n247: // +genclient:noStatus\n248: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n249: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n250: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=agentruntimes,shortName=ar;ars,singular=agentruntime,categories={agentcube,all}\n251: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n252: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase of the agent runtime\"\n253: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Sandbox\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.sandboxId`,description=\"ID of the sandbox pod\"\n254: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n255: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Message\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.message`,priority=1\n256: \n257: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n258: // An AgentRuntime represents a sandbox instance for running AI agents.\n259: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n260: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n261: type AgentRuntime struct {\n262: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n263: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n264: \n265: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the AgentRuntime.\n266: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n267: \tSpec AgentRuntimeSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n268: \n269: \t// Status defines the observed state of the AgentRuntime.\n270: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n271: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n272: }\n273: \n274: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n275: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n276: \n277: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime resources.\n278: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n279: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n280: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n281: \n282: \t// Items is the list of AgentRuntime resources.\n283: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n284: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n285: }\n\n(End of file - total 285 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go","time":{"start":1775841816012,"end":1775841816036}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841816041,"sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","part":{"id":"prt_d786ba94800105bCQcfNyzddSb","messageID":"msg_d786b930b00120r4eikhbU3AIX","sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type ProtocolType string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n31: \tProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n32: \n33: \t// ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n34: \tProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n35: )\n36: \n37: // AuthModeType represents the authentication mode for the CodeInterpreter.\n38: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n39: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n40: type AuthModeType string\n41: \n42: const (\n43: \t// AuthModePicoD represents authentication using PicoD.\n44: \tAuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n45: \n46: \t// AuthModeNone represents no authentication.\n47: \tAuthModeNone AuthModeType = \"none\"\n48: )\n49: \n50: // TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n51: // This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\n52: type TargetPort struct {\n53: \t// PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n54: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n55: \tPathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n56: \n57: \t// Name is an optional name for this port.\n58: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n59: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n60: \n61: \t// Port is the port number to expose.\n62: \t// This field is required.\n63: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n64: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n65: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n66: \tPort uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n67: \n68: \t// Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n69: \t// Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n70: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n72: \tProtocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n73: }\n74: \n75: // CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a CodeInterpreter sandbox.\n76: // It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n77: type CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n78: \t// Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n79: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n80: \t// +mapType=atomic\n81: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n82: \n83: \t// Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n84: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n85: \t// +mapType=atomic\n86: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n87: \n88: \t// Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n89: \t// This field is required.\n90: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n91: \tSpec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n92: }\n93: \n94: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n95: // This specification describes the configuration for a code interpreter sandbox instance\n96: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n97: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \t// +listType=map\n100: \t// +listMapKey=port\n101: \tPorts []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n102: \n103: \t// Template is the sandbox template containing the pod specification.\n104: \t// This field is required.\n105: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n106: \tTemplate *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n107: \n108: \t// SessionTimeout specifies the session timeout duration.\n109: \t// Defaults to \"15m\" if not specified.\n110: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n111: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n112: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// MaxSessionDuration specifies the maximum session duration.\n115: \t// Defaults to \"8h\" if not specified.\n116: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n117: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n118: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n119: \n120: \t// WarmPoolSize specifies the number of warm sandbox instances to maintain.\n121: \t// If not specified, no warm pool is maintained.\n122: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n123: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n124: \tWarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// AuthMode specifies the authentication mode for the sandbox.\n127: \t// Defaults to \"picod\" if not specified.\n128: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n129: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"picod\"\n130: \tAuthMode AuthModeType `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n131: }\n132: \n133: // CodeInterpreterConditionType represents a condition type for CodeInterpreter.\n134: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n135: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n136: type CodeInterpreterConditionType string\n137: \n138: const (\n139: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionReady indicates the CodeInterpreter is ready to accept requests.\n140: \tCodeInterpreterConditionReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Ready\"\n141: \n142: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n143: \tCodeInterpreterConditionSandboxCreated CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n144: \n145: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n146: \tCodeInterpreterConditionSandboxReady CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n147: \n148: \t// CodeInterpreterConditionFailed indicates the CodeInterpreter has failed.\n149: \tCodeInterpreterConditionFailed CodeInterpreterConditionType = \"Failed\"\n150: )\n151: \n152: // CodeInterpreterCondition represents a condition of a CodeInterpreter.\n153: type CodeInterpreterCondition struct {\n154: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n156: \tType CodeInterpreterConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n157: \n158: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n159: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n160: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n161: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n162: \n163: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n164: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n165: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n166: \n167: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n174: }\n175: \n176: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n177: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n178: // state of the sandbox instance.\n179: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n180: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \t// +listType=map\n183: \t// +listMapKey=type\n184: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n185: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n186: \tConditions []CodeInterpreterCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// Ready indicates whether the CodeInterpreter is ready to accept requests.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tReady *bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n191: }\n192: \n193: // +genclient\n194: // +genclient:noStatus\n195: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n196: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n197: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n198: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n199: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n200: \n201: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n202: // A CodeInterpreter represents a sandbox instance for running code interpretation workloads.\n203: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n204: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n205: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n206: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n207: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n208: \n209: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the CodeInterpreter.\n210: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n211: \tSpec CodeInterpreterSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n212: \n213: \t// Status defines the observed state of the CodeInterpreter.\n214: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n215: \tStatus CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n216: }\n217: \n218: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n219: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n220: \n221: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n222: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n223: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n224: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n225: \n226: \t// Items is the list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n227: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n228: \tItems []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n229: }\n\n(End of file - total 229 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go","time":{"start":1775841816014,"end":1775841816038}}}}
