{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842027267,"sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","part":{"id":"prt_d786bee96001ParMwx7cq7aLuw","messageID":"msg_d786bd766001iamXhmjp4o4E9Q","sessionID":"ses_28794bd2fffeS6HtSdoXIGqVQ2","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-003 Design: CRD Shared Types and Constants (client-go)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-003  \n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small  \n\nGenerate the Kubernetes client-go library for the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The generated client provides programmatic access to `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs, including typed clients, informers, and listers.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\nThe client-go library follows the standard Kubernetes code-generation pattern, providing a layered architecture for interacting with custom resources:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           Consumer Applications                              │\n│  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │\n│  │   Controllers │  │    CLI Tools  │  │  Workload Mgr │  │   Test Mocks │ │\n│  └───────┬───────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └───────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘ │\n└──────────┼──────────────────┼──────────────────┼─────────────────┼─────────┘\n           │                  │                  │                 │\n           ▼                  ▼                  ▼                 ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           client-go Library                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                        Clientset (Interface)                          │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │                    RuntimeV1alpha1Interface                     │  │   │\n│  │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ AgentRuntimeInterface│  │    CodeInterpreterInterface     │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Create()          │  │  · Create()                     │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Get()             │  │  · Get()                        │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · List()            │  │  · List()                       │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Watch()           │  │  · Watch()                      │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Update()          │  │  · Update()                     │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · UpdateStatus()    │  │  · UpdateStatus()               │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Delete()          │  │  · Delete()                     │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Patch()           │  │  · Patch()                      │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                     SharedInformerFactory                             │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ AgentRuntimeInformer│  │    CodeInterpreterInformer      │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Informer()        │  │  · Informer()                   │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  │ · Lister()          │  │  · Lister()                     │  │  │   │\n│  │  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘  │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      Lister Interfaces                                │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐        │   │\n│  │  │ AgentRuntimeLister  │  │    CodeInterpreterLister        │        │   │\n│  │  │ · List()            │  │  · List()                       │        │   │\n│  │  │ · AgentRuntimes()   │  │  · CodeInterpreters()           │        │   │\n│  │  │   (namespace lister)│  │    (namespace lister)           │        │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────────┘        │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Scheme / Codecs (register.go)                      │   │\n│  │  · AddToScheme()  · Scheme  · Codecs  · ParameterCodec               │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **Clientset** | Entry point for all API operations | `*rest.Config` | Typed clients per group-version |\n| **Typed Client** | CRUD operations for specific resource | Context, resource object | Result object, error |\n| **Informer** | Watch and cache resources | Client, resync period | `cache.SharedIndexInformer` |\n| **Lister** | Read-only cached access | Label selectors | Cached resource list |\n| **Scheme** | Type registration and serialization | Raw bytes/Objects | Typed objects |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Clientset\n\n#### Interface Definition\n\n```go\n// Interface provides access to the AgentCube API clientset.\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n#### Clientset Struct\n\n```go\n// Clientset contains the clients for groups. Each group has exactly one\n// version included in a Clientset.\ntype Clientset struct {\n    *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n    runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n}\n```\n\n#### Constructors\n\n| Function | Signature | Description |\n|----------|-----------|-------------|\n| `NewForConfig` | `func(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)` | Creates clientset from REST config |\n| `NewForConfigAndClient` | `func(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)` | Creates with custom HTTP client |\n| `NewForConfigOrDie` | `func(c *rest.Config) *Clientset` | Creates or panics on error |\n| `New` | `func(c rest.Interface) *Clientset` | Creates from REST interface |\n\n### Typed Client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n#### RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n\n```go\n// RuntimeV1alpha1Interface provides access to runtime/v1alpha1 resources.\ntype RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n    RESTClient() rest.Interface\n    AgentRuntimesGetter\n    CodeInterpretersGetter\n}\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimesGetter / AgentRuntimeInterface\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimesGetter provides access to AgentRuntime resources.\ntype AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n}\n\n// AgentRuntimeInterface provides CRUD operations for AgentRuntime resources.\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\n**REST Resource:** `agentruntimes` (plural)\n\n#### CodeInterpretersGetter / CodeInterpreterInterface\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpretersGetter provides access to CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpretersGetter interface {\n    CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterInterface\n}\n\n// CodeInterpreterInterface provides CRUD operations for CodeInterpreter resources.\ntype CodeInterpreterInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    CodeInterpreterExpansion\n}\n```\n\n**REST Resource:** `codeinterpreters` (plural)\n\n#### Expansion Hooks\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeExpansion allows adding custom methods to AgentRuntimeInterface.\ntype AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n\n// CodeInterpreterExpansion allows adding custom methods to CodeInterpreterInterface.\ntype CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n```\n\n### Scheme\n\n#### Package: `clientset/versioned/scheme/`\n\n```go\n// Package scheme contains the scheme registration for the runtime/v1alpha1 API group.\n\nvar (\n    // Scheme is the runtime.Scheme to which types are registered.\n    Scheme = runtime.NewScheme()\n\n    // Codecs provides access to the encoder and decoder for this scheme.\n    Codecs = serializer.NewCodecFactory(Scheme)\n\n    // ParameterCodec handles parameter encoding/decoding.\n    ParameterCodec = runtime.NewParameterCodec(Scheme)\n)\n\n// AddToScheme adds runtime/v1alpha1 types to the given scheme.\nfunc AddToScheme(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error\n```\n\n### Informer Factory\n\n#### SharedInformerFactory Interface\n\n```go\n// SharedInformerFactory provides access to shared informers for resources.\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {\n    internalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n    Start(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n    Shutdown()\n    WaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n    ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n    InformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Runtime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n}\n```\n\n#### Factory Options\n\n```go\n// SharedInformerOption configures the SharedInformerFactory.\ntype SharedInformerOption func(*sharedInformerFactory)\n\n// Available options:\nfunc WithCustomResyncConfig(config map[v1.Object]time.Duration) SharedInformerOption\nfunc WithTweakListOptions(tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) SharedInformerOption\nfunc WithNamespace(namespace string) SharedInformerOption\nfunc WithTransform(transform cache.TransformFunc) SharedInformerOption\n```\n\n#### Factory Constructors\n\n| Function | Signature |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `NewSharedInformerFactory` | `func(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration) SharedInformerFactory` |\n| `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` | `func(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration, options ...SharedInformerOption) SharedInformerFactory` |\n\n### Per-Type Informers\n\n#### AgentRuntimeInformer\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeInformer provides access to AgentRuntime informers.\ntype AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n    Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n}\n\n// Constructor functions:\nfunc NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers) cache.SharedIndexInformer\nfunc NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers, tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterInformer\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterInformer provides access to CodeInterpreter informers.\ntype CodeInterpreterInformer interface {\n    Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    Lister() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister\n}\n\n// Constructor functions:\nfunc NewCodeInterpreterInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers) cache.SharedIndexInformer\nfunc NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer(client versioned.Interface, namespace string, resyncPeriod time.Duration, indexers cache.Indexers, tweakListOptions internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n```\n\n### Listers\n\n#### AgentRuntimeLister\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeLister provides read-only access to AgentRuntime list.\ntype AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n    AgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n}\n\n// AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister provides namespaced listing.\ntype AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreterLister\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterLister provides read-only access to CodeInterpreter list.\ntype CodeInterpreterLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    CodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n    CodeInterpreterListerExpansion\n}\n\n// CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister provides namespaced listing.\ntype CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister interface {\n    List(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Get(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    CodeInterpreterNamespaceListerExpansion\n}\n```\n\n### Fake Clientset (for Testing)\n\n```go\n// Package fake provides a fake clientset for testing.\n\n// NewSimpleClientset returns a clientset that will respond with the provided objects.\nfunc NewSimpleClientset(objs ...runtime.Object) *Clientset\n\n// NewClientset returns a clientset that uses the provided scheme.\nfunc NewClientset(scheme *runtime.Scheme, tracker testing.ObjectTracker) *Clientset\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### REST Resource Mappings\n\n| Resource | API Group | Version | Kind | Plural | Short Names |\n|----------|-----------|---------|------|--------|-------------|\n| AgentRuntime | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `AgentRuntime` | `agentruntimes` | `ar`, `ars` |\n| CodeInterpreter | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `CodeInterpreter` | `codeinterpreters` | `ci`, `cis` |\n\n### HTTP Endpoints\n\n#### AgentRuntime Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List |\n| POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update |\n| PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Patch |\n| DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get Status |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Update Status |\n\n#### CodeInterpreter Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List |\n| POST | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update |\n| PATCH | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Patch |\n| DELETE | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete |\n| GET | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get Status |\n| PUT | `/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update Status |\n\n### Generic Resource Routing\n\n```go\n// ForResource returns a GenericInformer for the specified resource.\nfunc (f *sharedInformerFactory) ForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error) {\n    switch resource {\n    case v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"):\n        return &genericInformer{resource: resource.GroupResource(), informer: f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()}, nil\n    case v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\"):\n        return &genericInformer{resource: resource.GroupResource(), informer: f.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()}, nil\n    default:\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no informer found for %v\", resource)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Source | Handling Strategy |\n|----------|--------|-------------------|\n| **Connection Errors** | REST client, network layer | Retry with exponential backoff |\n| **API Errors** | Kubernetes API server | Check error type with `apierrors` helpers |\n| **Validation Errors** | API server validation | Return 422, examine error details |\n| **Not Found** | Resource doesn't exist | Check `apierrors.IsNotFound(err)` |\n| **Conflict** | Resource version mismatch | Retry after re-fetching resource |\n| **Forbidden** | RBAC denied | Log and alert, escalate permissions |\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Typed Client Error Handling\n\n```go\n// Example: Handling errors from AgentRuntime client\nfunc (c *Controller) reconcileAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, name, namespace string) error {\n    ar, err := c.client.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            // Resource was deleted - clean up\n            return c.handleDeleted(name)\n        }\n        if apierrors.IsTimeout(err) {\n            // Temporary error - retry later\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"timeout fetching AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n        }\n        // Other errors - wrap and return\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    // Process the resource\n    return c.processAgentRuntime(ar)\n}\n```\n\n#### Informer Error Handling\n\n```go\n// Example: Setting up error handlers for informers\nfunc (c *Controller) setupInformers() {\n    agentRuntimeInformer := c.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n    \n    // Add event handlers\n    agentRuntimeInformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n        AddFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeAdd,\n        UpdateFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeUpdate,\n        DeleteFunc: c.onAgentRuntimeDelete,\n    })\n\n    // Handle informer errors\n    agentRuntimeInformer.SetWatchErrorHandler(func(r *cache.Reflector, err error) {\n        klog.Errorf(\"AgentRuntime watch error: %v\", err)\n        // Metrics and alerting\n        metrics.RecordWatchError(\"agentruntime\", err)\n    })\n}\n```\n\n#### Lister Error Handling\n\n```go\n// Example: Handling lister errors (should be rare, usually cache is synced)\nfunc (c *Controller) listAgentRuntimes(selector labels.Selector) ([]*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n    runtimes, err := c.agentRuntimeLister.List(selector)\n    if err != nil {\n        // This is typically a programming error or cache not synced\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list AgentRuntimes from cache: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return runtimes, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Error Propagation Best Practices\n\n1. **Always wrap errors** with context using `fmt.Errorf(\"...: %w\", err)`\n2. **Check specific error types** using `apierrors` helpers before wrapping\n3. **Log at appropriate levels** - debug for retryable, error for permanent\n4. **Use structured logging** with resource identifiers\n5. **Return early** on unrecoverable errors\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Fake Clientset Tests\n\n```go\n// Test using fake clientset for AgentRuntime operations\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeCreate(t *testing.T) {\n    // Create fake clientset\n    client := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n\n    // Create a test AgentRuntime\n    ar := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-ar\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image: \"agent:latest\",\n        },\n    }\n\n    // Create the resource\n    created, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-ar\", created.Name)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"agent:latest\", created.Spec.Image)\n\n    // Verify it exists\n    fetched, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(context.Background(), \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, created.UID, fetched.UID)\n}\n```\n\n#### Fake Lister Tests\n\n```go\n// Test using fake listers\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeLister(t *testing.T) {\n    // Create fake objects\n    ar1 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar1\", Namespace: \"ns1\"}}\n    ar2 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar2\", Namespace: \"ns1\"}}\n    ar3 := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"ar3\", Namespace: \"ns2\"}}\n\n    // Create indexer\n    indexer := cache.NewIndexer(cache.MetaNamespaceKeyFunc, cache.Indexers{cache.NamespaceIndex: cache.MetaNamespaceIndexFunc})\n    indexer.Add(ar1)\n    indexer.Add(ar2)\n    indexer.Add(ar3)\n\n    // Create lister\n    lister := runtimev1alpha1.NewAgentRuntimeLister(indexer)\n\n    // Test List all\n    all, err := lister.List(labels.Everything())\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Len(t, all, 3)\n\n    // Test List by namespace\n    ns1Runtimes, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(\"ns1\").List(labels.Everything())\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Len(t, ns1Runtimes, 2)\n\n    // Test Get\n    ar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(\"ns1\").Get(\"ar1\")\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"ar1\", ar.Name)\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\n// Integration test using real API server (envtest)\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup envtest\n    testEnv := &envtest.Environment{\n        CRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\"../../config/crd/bases\"},\n    }\n    cfg, err := testEnv.Start()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer testEnv.Stop()\n\n    // Create clientset\n    client, err := clientset.NewForConfig(cfg)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    ctx := context.Background()\n\n    // Create namespace\n    k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(cfg)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    _, err = k8sClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().Create(ctx, &corev1.Namespace{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test-ns\"},\n    }, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Create AgentRuntime\n    ar := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-ar\",\n            Namespace: \"test-ns\",\n        },\n        Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image: \"test-image:latest\",\n        },\n    }\n    created, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Update status\n    created.Status.Phase = v1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning\n    updated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").UpdateStatus(ctx, created, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, v1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning, updated.Status.Phase)\n\n    // Delete\n    err = client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Verify deletion\n    _, err = client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n    assert.True(t, apierrors.IsNotFound(err))\n}\n```\n\n### Code Generation Verification\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# verify-codegen.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"=== Verifying client-go code generation ===\"\n\n# Generate code\necho \"Running code generation...\"\nmake gen-client\n\n# Build to verify compilation\necho \"Building generated code...\"\ngo build ./client-go/...\n\n# Run tests\necho \"Running client-go tests...\"\ngo test ./client-go/...\n\n# Check for uncommitted changes\nif [[ -n $(git status --porcelain client-go/) ]]; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Generated code is out of date. Run 'make gen-client' and commit changes.\"\n    git diff client-go/\n    exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"=== Verification passed ===\"\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Testing Method |\n|-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n| Clientset Interface | 90%+ | Unit tests with fakes |\n| Typed Clients | 85%+ | Unit tests with fakes |\n| Scheme Registration | 100% | Integration tests |\n| Informers | 80%+ | Integration tests |\n| Listers | 100% | Unit tests with fake indexers |\n| Fake Clientset | 100% | Self-testing via usage |\n\n### Continuous Integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/client-go.yaml\nname: client-go\n\non:\n  push:\n    paths:\n      - 'pkg/apis/**'\n      - 'client-go/**'\n      - 'hack/**'\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - 'pkg/apis/**'\n      - 'client-go/**'\n      - 'hack/**'\n\njobs:\n  verify:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Set up Go\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.23'\n\n      - name: Verify code generation\n        run: make verify-codegen\n\n      - name: Build client-go\n        run: go build ./client-go/...\n\n      - name: Test client-go\n        run: go test -v -race ./client-go/...\n\n      - name: Test with real types\n        run: go test -v ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\nclient-go/\n├── clientset/\n│   └── versioned/\n│       ├── clientset.go                    # Clientset struct and Interface\n│       ├── scheme/\n│       │   ├── doc.go                      # Package documentation\n│       │   └── register.go                 # Scheme registration\n│       ├── typed/\n│       │   └── runtime/\n│       │       └── v1alpha1/\n│       │           ├── doc.go              # Package documentation\n│       │           ├── runtime_client.go   # RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n│       │           ├── agentruntime.go     # AgentRuntimeInterface\n│       │           ├── codeinterpreter.go  # CodeInterpreterInterface\n│       │           ├── generated_expansion.go  # Expansion interfaces\n│       │           └── fake/\n│       │               ├── doc.go\n│       │               ├── fake_runtime_client.go\n│       │               ├── fake_agentruntime.go\n│       │               └── fake_codeinterpreter.go\n│       └── fake/\n│           ├── doc.go\n│           ├── clientset_generated.go      # Fake Clientset\n│           └── register.go\n├── informers/\n│   └── externalversions/\n│       ├── factory.go                      # SharedInformerFactory\n│       ├── generic.go                      # Generic informer routing\n│       ├── internalinterfaces/\n│       │   └── factory_interfaces.go       # Internal interfaces\n│       └── runtime/\n│           ├── interface.go                # Group interface\n│           └── v1alpha1/\n│               ├── interface.go            # Version interface\n│               ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntimeInformer\n│               └── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreterInformer\n└── listers/\n    └── runtime/\n        └── v1alpha1/\n            ├── agentruntime.go             # AgentRuntimeLister\n            ├── codeinterpreter.go          # CodeInterpreterLister\n            └── expansion_generated.go      # Lister expansion interfaces\n```\n\n---\n\n## Code Generation\n\n### Generation Tool: k8s.io/code-generator\n\n```bash\n# Makefile target for client generation\ngen-client:\n    ./hack/update-codegen.sh\n\n# Verification target\nverify-codegen:\n    ./hack/verify-codegen.sh\n```\n\n### Generation Script\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# hack/update-codegen.sh\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nSCRIPT_ROOT=$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")/..\nCODEGEN_PKG=${CODEGEN_PKG:-$(cd \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}\"; go list -m -f '{{.Dir}}' k8s.io/code-generator)}\n\n# Generate clientset, informers, listers\n\"${CODEGEN_PKG}/generate-groups.sh\" \\\n    \"client,informer,lister\" \\\n    github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go \\\n    github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis \\\n    \"runtime:v1alpha1\" \\\n    --go-header-file \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}/hack/boilerplate.go.txt\" \\\n    --output-base \"${SCRIPT_ROOT}\" \\\n    --with-watch\n```\n\n### Generation Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Value | Description |\n|-----------|-------|-------------|\n| Generators | `client,informer,lister` | What to generate |\n| Output Package | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Go import path |\n| API Package | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Source types location |\n| Groups | `runtime:v1alpha1` | Group:version pairs |\n| Flags | `--with-watch` | Enable Watch support |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, runtime.Object |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | REST client, informers, listers |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | Code generation tools |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Local | Source API types |\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### 1. Separate client-go Module\n\n**Decision**: Place generated code in `client-go/` directory with its own go.mod (optional).\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Consumers can depend only on the client without pulling in controller dependencies\n- Aligns with Kubernetes ecosystem conventions (e.g., `k8s.io/client-go`)\n- Cleaner dependency graph for external tools\n\n### 2. Standard Code Generator\n\n**Decision**: Use `k8s.io/code-generator` instead of custom tooling.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Industry standard for Kubernetes CRD clients\n- Automatic updates with Kubernetes version bumps\n- Well-tested and maintained by the community\n- Supports all required features (watch, informers, listers)\n\n### 3. Expansion Interfaces\n\n**Decision**: Generate empty expansion interfaces for all typed clients and listers.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Allows extending generated interfaces without modifying generated code\n- Follows Kubernetes client-go pattern\n- Enables custom helper methods while maintaining interface compatibility\n\n### 4. Fake Clientset\n\n**Decision**: Include complete fake implementation for all interfaces.\n\n**Rationale**:\n- Essential for unit testing controllers\n- Provides in-memory object tracking\n- Supports all CRUD operations including Watch\n- No external dependencies required for testing\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n- [code-generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n- [sample-controller](https://github.com/kubernetes/sample-controller) - Example usage pattern\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n\n| Version | Date | Changes |\n|---------|------|---------|\n| 1.0 | 2026-04-11 | Initial design for AR-003 client-go library |\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775842027051,"end":1775842027263}}}}
